Dividend Brief -- Crystal Brands Inc.:
   Firm Plans to Cut Dividend
   60% to Meet Loan Accords
Long-term note agreements with Prudential Insurance Co. of
America and Aetna Life  Casualty Co. also have been amended
to conform with the revised bank-loan covenants. All past
defaults on the notes have been waived, Crystal Brands said.
   The previous dividend, five cents a share, was last paid
Jan. 1. A spokesman said Crystal Brands' board will vote on
the dividend reduction at its meeting next month.